I can see the issue! The "show answers" functionality for the practice exams is defined but not properly connected to the HTML elements. Looking at your code, I can see the functions showExamAnswers() and checkExam() are defined, but they need to be properly linked to the buttons.

The problem is in the Practice Exam sections - the buttons are calling functions that need to be properly implemented. Here's the fix:

Replace the existing exam button sections (around line 3650-3700) with this corrected code:

```html
<div class="quiz-actions">
    <button class="quiz-action-button" onclick="checkExam(1)" aria-label="Check Exam 1 answers">Check Exam 1</button>
    <button class="quiz-action-button" onclick="showExamAnswers(1)" aria-label="Show Exam 1 answers">Show Answers</button>
    <button class="quiz-action-button" onclick="clearExamAnswers(1)" style="background-color: #9e9e9e;" aria-label="Clear Exam 1 answers">
        <i class="fas fa-eraser" aria-hidden="true"></i> Clear Answers
    </button>
</div>
```

And make sure this enhanced version of the showExamAnswers function is in your JavaScript (around line 4800):

```javascript
// Enhanced exam functions with model answers
function showExamAnswers(examNum) {
    const examContainers = document.querySelectorAll(`#section9 .quiz-container`);
    
    // Find the correct exam container (they're indexed by order)
    let examIndex = examNum - 1;
    if (examIndex >= 0 && examIndex < examContainers.length) {
        const examContainer = examContainers[examIndex];
        const questionContainers = examContainer.querySelectorAll('.question-container');
        
        questionContainers.forEach((container, index) => {
            // Get the correct answer div
            const correctDiv = container.querySelector('.correct-answer');
            if (correctDiv) {
                // Show the correct answer div
                correctDiv.style.display = 'block';
                
                // Create or update feedback div
                let feedbackDiv = container.querySelector('.answer-feedback.model-answer');
                if (!feedbackDiv) {
                    feedbackDiv = document.createElement('div');
                    feedbackDiv.className = 'answer-feedback correct model-answer';
                    container.appendChild(feedbackDiv);
                }
                
                // Get the correct answer text
                const correctText = correctDiv.textContent.replace('Correct answer:', '').trim();
                feedbackDiv.innerHTML = `<i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> <strong>Model Answer:</strong> ${correctText}`;
                feedbackDiv.style.display = 'flex';
            }
        });
        
        // Show results message
        const resultsDiv = document.getElementById(`exam${examNum}-results`);
        if (resultsDiv) {
            resultsDiv.style.display = 'block';
            resultsDiv.innerHTML = `
                <div class="quiz-score">Exam ${examNum} Model Answers</div>
                <p><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> Model answers are displayed below each question. Review them carefully to understand the correct responses.</p>
            `;
        }
    }
}
```

Also, make sure the correct-answer divs in your practice exams have the right content. They should look like this:

```html
<div class="correct-answer" style="display: none;">Correct answer: b) Eucalyptus globulus</div>
```

The issue was that the showExamAnswers function wasn't properly implemented to display the hidden correct answers. The fix above will:

1. Find all question containers in the selected exam
2. Locate the hidden correct-answer divs
3. Display them
4. Add visual feedback showing the model answers

This should make the "Show Answers" buttons work correctly for all three practice exams.
